{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, the LLM must reproduce the existing measurement process everywhere-for every dataset and for every task.",
    "This assumption, stated so directly, is as a conceptual matter unlikely to be true.",
    "As an empirical matter, the assumption of no measurement error contradicts even the most optimistic results of benchmark evaluations of LLM performance as reported by either tech companies or computer science researchers.",
    "We extend that evidence here by empirically illustrating the severity of the implications of LLM measurement error for downstream economic parameter estimation.",
    "In both of our empirical applications (financial news headlines and Congressional legislation), we show that seemingly minor implementation choices such as which LLM to use or how to prompt the model affect not only the labels the LLM assigns to a given piece of text, but also substantially affect the size, significance and even sign of economic parameters estimated using those LLM labels."
  ]
}